  "url": "https://www.lankadeepa.lk/news/\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf-\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1-\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8-\u0db4\u0dde\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0d9a-\u0d85\u0d82\u0dc1\u0dba\u0da7/101-615590",
  "time_ut": 1656486011,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db4\u0dde\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d85\u0d82\u0dc1\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Importation of aviation fuel to the private sector",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Cabinet paper submitted by the Minister of Ports, Shipping and Aviation Nimal Siripala de Silva to approve the import of jet fuel has been approved by the Cabinet.",
        "The Minister has submitted this cabinet paper considering the difficulty in supplying aviation fuel to the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation due to the foreign exchange crisis.",
        "Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said that he presented this Cabinet paper after a discussion held at the Ministry on the 24th with the representatives of the airlines and the fuel warehouses in Sri Lanka regarding the severe crisis that has arisen in obtaining jet fuel for aircraft arriving in Sri Lanka.",
        "Representatives of the airlines pointed out that some airlines have already reduced their flights to Sri Lanka due to the weakening of jet fuel storage in Sri Lanka.",
        "The Petroleum Corporation (CPC) has a monopoly on the importation of jet fuel into the country, and if it allows its agencies to import, store and sell jet fuel, it will be able to do so, the warehouses said.",
        "The Minister stressed that if the arrival of aircraft is further reduced in the face of the exchange crisis, the existing rules should be amended or this opportunity should be overcome as it will severely affect the tourism industry, exports, foreign investment as well as those going for employment abroad from Sri Lanka.",
        "As it will take some time to amend these Acts, the Minister has decided to allow private sector fuel warehouses to import fuel with the approval of the Cabinet as a policy decision of the Government for a short period of time.",
        "The Minister instructed the Civil Aviation Authority and the Aviation Authority to extend their fullest support to this task and the Cabinet pointed out that other Cabinet agencies including the Customs and Petroleum Corporation should also provide assistance in this regard.",
        "Taisei, which is constructing the second terminal at the Katunayake International Airport, is also facing a fuel crisis, the Minister said.",
        "Secretary to the Ministry KD Retired Major General GA Chandrasiri, Chairman, H Ruwanchandra Airport and Airlines; Capt. Themiya Abeywickrema, Director General, Civil Aviation Authority;"
      ],
